<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-08T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="75" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./30: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-08T22:00:00+03:00">April 8,
                                    1934—10 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 8—8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>45. Supplementing my 43, April 8, 7 p.m., <persName corresp="#p_UKA1">Umansky</persName>, chief of Foreign Office Press Department,
                            called in American correspondents this afternoon and gave lengthy
                            prepared statement on subject of Johnson bill and Soviet-American
                            relations. It contained so many phrases used to me by <persName corresp="#p_LMM1">Litvinov</persName> that I believed it was
                            dictated by the latter. <persName corresp="#p_UKA1">Umansky</persName>
                            refused to allow quotation or attribution to any official Soviet source.
                                <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Herald
                                Tribune</hi> will carry story.</p>
                        <p>If Department approves course suggested in my 43, April 8, 7 p.m., think
                            it well to refuse comment on this trial balloon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>